A child and a security guard were injured following a multi vehicle crash on the P200 between KwaGamalakhe and Shelly Beach. The Netcare 911 media liaison officer, Shawn Herbst said reports from the scene indicate that six vehicle were involved in a collision, completely obstructing the road. Herbst said paramedics assessed the scene and found that a minor male and an adult male sustained minor injury. "Both patients were treated on scene and transported by ambulance to hospital for further treatment," said Herbst. 